# Part 4 – Build a Better Blood Report Analyzer (20 minutes)

Let's improve yesterday's program.

We'll classify HbA1c into three categories.

For learning purposes, use these simplified thresholds:

| HbA1c         | Status      |
| ------------- | ----------- |
| Less than 5.7 | Normal      |
| 5.7 to 6.4    | Prediabetes |
| 6.5 or higher | Diabetes    |

Type this:

```python
hba1c = float(input("Enter HbA1c: "))

if hba1c < 5.7:
    print("Status: Normal")

elif hba1c < 6.5:
    print("Status: Prediabetes")

else:
    print("Status: Diabetes")
```

